		<header>
			
			<h1>Increase in cotton production in West and Central Africa despite poor early rains</h1>

			
			<h4>
												02 February 2014
										</h4>

					</header>


		
		
					<p>According to a USDA report, the West African 2013/14 cotton season (August to July) started late as a result of irregular rains, requiring farmers to replant.</p><p><b>West African seed cotton production tonnes for marketing years 2011/12–2013/14</b></p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
